{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":880,"text":"I'm here to recruit men\nto support gender equality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":4480,"text":"(Cheers)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":7640,"text":"Wait, wait. What?"},{"time":10680,"text":"What do men have to do\nwith gender equality?"},{"time":13520,"text":"Gender equality is about women, right?"},{"time":15520,"text":"I mean, the word gender is about women."},{"time":20200,"text":"Actually, I'm even here speaking\nas a middle class white man."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24520,"text":"Now, I wasn't always\na middle class white man."},{"time":27440,"text":"It all happened for me about 30 years ago\nwhen I was in graduate school,"},{"time":32640,"text":"and a bunch of us graduate students\ngot together one day,"},{"time":36080,"text":"and we said, you know,\nthere's an explosion"},{"time":38760,"text":"of writing and thinking\nin feminist theory,"},{"time":42520,"text":"but there's no courses yet."},{"time":44440,"text":"So we did what graduate students\ntypically do in a situation like that."},{"time":47798,"text":"We said, OK, let's have a study group."},{"time":50480,"text":"We'll read a text, we'll talk about it,"},{"time":53080,"text":"we'll have a potluck dinner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":56200,"text":"So every week,\n11 women and me got together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59720,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":62520,"text":"We would read some text in feminist theory\nand have a conversation about it."},{"time":66480,"text":"And during one of our conversations,"},{"time":68720,"text":"I witnessed an interaction\nthat changed my life forever."},{"time":73640,"text":"It was a conversation between two women."},{"time":76640,"text":"One of the women was white,\nand one was black."},{"time":80920,"text":"And the white woman said --"},{"time":82280,"text":"this is going to sound\nvery anachronistic now --"},{"time":84640,"text":"the white woman said, \"All women\nface the same oppression as women."},{"time":90360,"text":"All women are similarly\nsituated in patriarchy,"},{"time":93200,"text":"and therefore all women have a kind\nof intuitive solidarity or sisterhood.\""},{"time":98840,"text":"And the black woman said,\n\"I'm not so sure."},{"time":102400,"text":"Let me ask you a question.\""},{"time":104320,"text":"So the black woman\nsays to the white woman,"},{"time":107080,"text":"\"When you wake up in the morning\nand you look in the mirror,"},{"time":109960,"text":"what do you see?\""},{"time":111200,"text":"And the white woman said, \"I see a woman.\""},{"time":113840,"text":"And the black woman said,\n\"You see, that's the problem for me."},{"time":117040,"text":"Because when I wake up in the morning\nand I look in the mirror,\" she said,"},{"time":120560,"text":"\"I see a black woman."},{"time":121960,"text":"To me, race is visible. But to you,\nrace is invisible. You don't see it.\""},{"time":127760,"text":"And then she said\nsomething really startling."},{"time":130479,"text":"She said, \"That's how privilege works."},{"time":133160,"text":"Privilege is invisible\nto those who have it.\""},{"time":136680,"text":"It is a luxury, I will say\nto the white people sitting in this room,"},{"time":139960,"text":"not to have to think about race\nevery split second of our lives."},{"time":143720,"text":"Privilege is invisible\nto those who have it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147480,"text":"Now remember, I was\nthe only man in this group,"},{"time":149880,"text":"so when I witnessed this, I went, \"Oh no.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":152800,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":154560,"text":"And somebody said,\n\"Well what was that reaction?\""},{"time":156920,"text":"And I said, \"Well, when I wake up\nin the morning and I look in the mirror,"},{"time":160600,"text":"I see a human being."},{"time":162520,"text":"I'm kind of the generic person."},{"time":165000,"text":"You know, I'm a middle class white man.\nI have no race, no class, no gender."},{"time":169040,"text":"I'm universally generalizable.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":171080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":172920,"text":"So I like to think that was the moment\nI became a middle class white man,"},{"time":176680,"text":"that class and race and gender\nwere not about other people,"},{"time":180640,"text":"they were about me."},{"time":182200,"text":"I had to start thinking about them,"},{"time":184400,"text":"and it had been privilege that had\nkept it invisible to me for so long."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189200,"text":"Now, I wish I could tell you\nthis story ends 30 years ago"},{"time":191891,"text":"in that little discussion group,"},{"time":193480,"text":"but I was reminded of it quite recently\nat my university where I teach."},{"time":197280,"text":"I have a colleague, and she and I\nboth teach the sociology of gender course"},{"time":201240,"text":"on alternate semesters."},{"time":203120,"text":"So she gives a guest lecture\nfor me when I teach."},{"time":205520,"text":"I give a guest lecture\nfor her when she teaches."},{"time":207920,"text":"So I walk into her class\nto give a guest lecture,"},{"time":211280,"text":"about 300 students in the room,"},{"time":213480,"text":"and as I walk in, one of the students\nlooks up and says,"},{"time":216840,"text":"\"Oh, finally, an objective opinion.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":220840,"text":"All that semester, whenever\nmy colleague opened her mouth,"},{"time":224000,"text":"what my students saw was a woman."},{"time":226400,"text":"I mean, if you were to say to my students,"},{"time":228520,"text":"\"There is structural inequality\nbased on gender in the United States,\""},{"time":232000,"text":"they'd say, \"Well of course\nyou'd say that."},{"time":234040,"text":"You're a woman. You're biased.\""},{"time":235541,"text":"When I say it, they go,\n\"Wow, is that interesting."},{"time":238440,"text":"Is that going to be on the test?\nHow do you spell 'structural'?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":241464,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":243320,"text":"So I hope you all can see,"},{"time":245600,"text":"this is what objectivity looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248480,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":252240,"text":"Disembodied Western rationality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":258279,"text":"And that, by the way, is why I think\nmen so often wear ties."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":264080,"text":"Because if you are going to embody\ndisembodied Western rationality,"},{"time":268680,"text":"you need a signifier,"},{"time":270200,"text":"and what could be a better signifier\nof disembodied Western rationality"},{"time":274440,"text":"than a garment that at one end is a noose\nand the other end points to the genitals?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":278880,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":285640,"text":"That is mind-body dualism right there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292040,"text":"So making gender visible to men"},{"time":296200,"text":"is the first step to engaging men\nto support gender equality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301040,"text":"Now, when men first hear\nabout gender equality,"},{"time":303400,"text":"when they first start thinking about it,"},{"time":305329,"text":"they often think, many men think,"},{"time":307840,"text":"well, that's right,\nthat's fair, that's just,"},{"time":312120,"text":"that's the ethical imperative."},{"time":315120,"text":"But not all men."},{"time":316720,"text":"Some men think --\nthe lightning bolt goes off,"},{"time":319440,"text":"and they go, \"Oh my God,\nyes, gender equality,\""},{"time":322280,"text":"and they will immediately begin\nto mansplain to you your oppression."},{"time":327960,"text":"They see supporting gender equality\nsomething akin to the cavalry,"},{"time":332600,"text":"like, \"Thanks very much for bringing this\nto our attention, ladies,"},{"time":335767,"text":"we'll take it from here.\""},{"time":337320,"text":"This results in a syndrome that I like\nto call 'premature self-congratulation.'"}]},{"cues":[{"time":341760,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":346080,"text":"There's another group, though,\nthat actively resists gender equality,"},{"time":350200,"text":"that sees gender equality\nas something that is detrimental to men."},{"time":355920,"text":"I was on a TV talk show\nopposite four white men."},{"time":359760,"text":"This is the beginning of the book\nI wrote, 'Angry White Men.'"},{"time":362960,"text":"These were four angry white men"},{"time":364680,"text":"who believed that they,\nwhite men in America,"},{"time":368560,"text":"were the victims of reverse discrimination\nin the workplace."},{"time":373840,"text":"And they all told stories\nabout how they were qualified for jobs,"},{"time":376920,"text":"qualified for promotions,"},{"time":378160,"text":"they didn't get them,\nthey were really angry."},{"time":380440,"text":"And the reason I'm telling you this\nis I want you to hear the title"},{"time":383640,"text":"of this particular show."},{"time":385320,"text":"It was a quote from one of the men,"},{"time":387480,"text":"and the quote was,"},{"time":388920,"text":"\"A Black Woman Stole My Job.\""},{"time":392360,"text":"And they all told their stories,"},{"time":393960,"text":"qualified for jobs,\nqualified for promotions,"},{"time":396120,"text":"didn't get it, really angry."},{"time":397480,"text":"And then it was my turn to speak,"},{"time":399280,"text":"and I said, \"I have\njust one question for you guys,"},{"time":401880,"text":"and it's about the title of the show,"},{"time":404520,"text":"'A Black Woman Stole My Job.'"},{"time":406400,"text":"Actually, it's about\none word in the title."},{"time":409320,"text":"I want to know about the word 'my.'"},{"time":411880,"text":"Where did you get the idea\nit was your job?"},{"time":415280,"text":"Why isn't the title of the show,\n'A Black Woman Got the Job?'"},{"time":418600,"text":"or 'A Black Woman Got A Job?'\""},{"time":421080,"text":"Because without confronting\nmen's sense of entitlement,"},{"time":424240,"text":"I don't think we'll ever understand\nwhy so many men resist gender equality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428560,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":435000,"text":"Look, we think this\nis a level playing field,"},{"time":438360,"text":"so any policy that tilts it\neven a little bit,"},{"time":440560,"text":"we think, \"Oh my God,\nwater's rushing uphill."},{"time":442720,"text":"It's reverse discrimination against us.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":444649,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":445880,"text":"So let me be very clear:"},{"time":447880,"text":"white men in Europe and the United States"},{"time":450920,"text":"are the beneficiaries of the single\ngreatest affirmative action program"},{"time":454960,"text":"in the history of the world."},{"time":456520,"text":"It is called \"the history of the world.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":458600,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":464760,"text":"So, now I've established\nsome of the obstacles to engaging men,"},{"time":469000,"text":"but why should we support gender equality?"},{"time":471640,"text":"Of course, it's fair,\nit's right and it's just."},{"time":475120,"text":"But more than that,"},{"time":476600,"text":"gender equality is also\nin our interest as men."},{"time":481520,"text":"If you listen to what men say\nabout what they want in their lives,"},{"time":486400,"text":"gender equality is actually a way\nfor us to get the lives we want to live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491960,"text":"Gender equality is good for countries."},{"time":495520,"text":"It turns out, according to most studies,"},{"time":499600,"text":"that those countries\nthat are the most gender equal"},{"time":502600,"text":"are also the countries that score highest\non the happiness scale."},{"time":507160,"text":"And that's not just because\nthey're all in Europe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":510800,"text":"Even within Europe, those countries\nthat are more gender equal"},{"time":514559,"text":"also have the highest levels of happiness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518320,"text":"It is also good for companies."},{"time":520880,"text":"Research by Catalyst and others\nhas shown conclusively"},{"time":524480,"text":"that the more gender-equal companies are,"},{"time":528120,"text":"the better it is for workers,"},{"time":532360,"text":"the happier their labor force is."},{"time":534200,"text":"They have lower job turnover.\nThey have lower levels of attrition."},{"time":538080,"text":"They have an easier time recruiting."},{"time":540440,"text":"They have higher rates of retention,\nhigher job satisfaction,"},{"time":543400,"text":"higher rates of productivity."},{"time":545640,"text":"So the question I'm often asked\nin companies is,"},{"time":548520,"text":"\"Boy, this gender equality thing,\nthat's really going to be expensive, huh?\""},{"time":552116,"text":"And I say, \"Oh no, in fact,\nwhat you have to start calculating"},{"time":556360,"text":"is how much gender inequality\nis already costing you."},{"time":560360,"text":"It is extremely expensive.\""},{"time":562880,"text":"So it is good for business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565640,"text":"And the other thing is, it's good for men."},{"time":569040,"text":"It is good for the kind of lives\nwe want to live,"},{"time":572040,"text":"because young men especially\nhave changed enormously,"},{"time":576000,"text":"and they want to have lives\nthat are animated"},{"time":579200,"text":"by terrific relationships\nwith their children."},{"time":581960,"text":"They expect their partners,\ntheir spouses, their wives,"},{"time":585720,"text":"to work outside the home"},{"time":586920,"text":"and be just as committed\nto their careers as they are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590440,"text":"I was talking, to give you\nan illustration of this change --"},{"time":594280,"text":"Some of you may remember this."},{"time":596080,"text":"When I was a lot younger,\nthere was a riddle that was posed to us."},{"time":601200,"text":"Some of you may wince\nto remember this riddle."},{"time":603640,"text":"This riddle went something like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606240,"text":"A man and his son\nare driving on the freeway,"},{"time":609600,"text":"and they're in a terrible accident,"},{"time":611600,"text":"and the father is killed,"},{"time":613880,"text":"and the son is brought\nto the hospital emergency room,"},{"time":616960,"text":"and as they're bringing the son\ninto the hospital emergency room,"},{"time":620040,"text":"the emergency room attending physician\nsees the boy and says,"},{"time":623680,"text":"\"Oh, I can't treat him, that's my son.\""},{"time":626040,"text":"How is this possible?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":628160,"text":"We were flummoxed by this."},{"time":630480,"text":"We could not figure this out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":632680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":634640,"text":"Well, I decided to do a little experiment\nwith my 16-year old son."},{"time":637800,"text":"He had a bunch of his friends\nhanging out at the house"},{"time":641280,"text":"watching a game on TV recently."},{"time":643600,"text":"So I decided I would pose\nthis riddle to them,"},{"time":645840,"text":"just to see, to gauge the level of change."},{"time":648840,"text":"Well, 16-year-old boys,"},{"time":650920,"text":"they immediately turned to me\nand said, \"It's his mom.\" Right?"},{"time":654960,"text":"No problem. Just like that."},{"time":656760,"text":"Except for my son, who said,\n\"Well, he could have two dads.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":659640,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":665160,"text":"That's an index, an indicator\nof how things have changed."},{"time":669000,"text":"Younger men today expect\nto be able to balance work and family."},{"time":674840,"text":"They want to be dual-career,\ndual-carer couples."},{"time":680160,"text":"They want to be able to balance\nwork and family with their partners."},{"time":683880,"text":"They want to be involved fathers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685800,"text":"Now, it turns out"},{"time":687960,"text":"that the more egalitarian\nour relationships,"},{"time":691360,"text":"the happier both partners are."},{"time":694960,"text":"Data from psychologists and sociologists\nare quite persuasive here."},{"time":698920,"text":"I think we have the persuasive numbers,\nthe data, to prove to men"},{"time":704600,"text":"that gender equality\nis not a zero-sum game, but a win-win."},{"time":708800,"text":"Here's what the data show."},{"time":710600,"text":"Now, when men begin\nthe process of engaging"},{"time":716160,"text":"with balancing work and family,"},{"time":717960,"text":"we often have two phrases\nthat we use to describe what we do."},{"time":721160,"text":"We pitch in and we help out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":723720,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":724960,"text":"And I'm going to propose\nsomething a little bit more radical,"},{"time":727880,"text":"one word: \"share.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":729120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":730880,"text":"Because here's what the data show:"},{"time":732560,"text":"when men share housework and childcare,"},{"time":734880,"text":"their children do better in school."},{"time":737600,"text":"Their children have lower rates\nof absenteeism,"},{"time":740240,"text":"higher rates of achievement."},{"time":741800,"text":"They are less likely\nto be diagnosed with ADHD."},{"time":744560,"text":"They are less likely\nto see a child psychiatrist."},{"time":747440,"text":"They are less likely\nto be put on medication."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750080,"text":"So when men share housework and childcare,"},{"time":753920,"text":"their children are happier and healthier,"},{"time":756720,"text":"and men want this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":759520,"text":"When men share housework and childcare,"},{"time":761960,"text":"their wives are happier. Duh."},{"time":765720,"text":"Not only that, their wives are healthier."},{"time":768200,"text":"Their wives are less likely\nto see a therapist,"},{"time":770415,"text":"less likely to be diagnosed\nwith depression,"},{"time":772487,"text":"less likely to be put on medication,\nmore likely to go to the gym,"},{"time":776280,"text":"report higher levels\nof marital satisfaction."},{"time":779360,"text":"So when men share housework and childcare,"},{"time":781400,"text":"their wives are happier and healthier,"},{"time":783280,"text":"and men certainly want this as well."},{"time":786760,"text":"When men share housework and childcare,"},{"time":788960,"text":"the men are healthier."},{"time":790720,"text":"They smoke less, drink less,\ntake recreational drugs less often."},{"time":794560,"text":"They are less likely to go to the ER"},{"time":797280,"text":"but more like to go to a doctor\nfor routine screenings."},{"time":800480,"text":"They are less likely to see a therapist,"},{"time":802440,"text":"less likely to be diagnosed\nwith depression,"},{"time":804560,"text":"less likely to be taking\nprescription medication."},{"time":807080,"text":"So when men share housework and childcare,"},{"time":809120,"text":"the men are happier and healthier."},{"time":812320,"text":"And who wouldn't want that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":814640,"text":"And finally,"},{"time":815920,"text":"when men share housework and childcare,"},{"time":817880,"text":"they have more sex."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":820560,"text":"Now, of these four fascinating findings,"},{"time":823000,"text":"which one do you think\nMen's Health magazine put on its cover?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":825960,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":828600,"text":"\"Housework Makes Her Horny."},{"time":831800,"text":"(Not When She Does It.)\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":833040,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":834720,"text":"Now, I will say,"},{"time":837000,"text":"just to remind the men in the audience,"},{"time":840000,"text":"these data were collected\nover a really long period of time,"},{"time":843840,"text":"so I don't want listeners to say,"},{"time":846680,"text":"\"Hmm, OK, I think\nI'll do the dishes tonight.\""},{"time":849720,"text":"These data were collected\nover a really long period of time."},{"time":853720,"text":"But I think it shows something important,"},{"time":857400,"text":"that when Men's Health magazine\nput it on their cover,"},{"time":859960,"text":"they also called,\nyou'll love this, \"Choreplay.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":863440,"text":"So, what we found\nis something really important,"},{"time":868240,"text":"that gender equality"},{"time":870360,"text":"is in the interest of countries,"},{"time":873440,"text":"of companies, and of men,"},{"time":876600,"text":"and their children and their partners,"},{"time":879160,"text":"that gender equality\nis not a zero-sum game."},{"time":881640,"text":"It's not a win-lose."},{"time":882920,"text":"It is a win-win for everyone."},{"time":886160,"text":"And what we also know"},{"time":888440,"text":"is we cannot fully empower women and girls"},{"time":892040,"text":"unless we engage boys and men."},{"time":894720,"text":"We know this."},{"time":897320,"text":"And my position is"},{"time":898800,"text":"that men need the very things\nthat women have identified"},{"time":903040,"text":"that they need to live the lives\nthey say they want to live"},{"time":906120,"text":"in order to live the lives\nthat we say we want to live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910600,"text":"In 1915, on the eve of one\nof the great suffrage demonstrations"},{"time":915840,"text":"down Fifth Avenue in New York City,"},{"time":917840,"text":"a writer in New York\nwrote an article in a magazine,"},{"time":921520,"text":"and the title of the article was,"},{"time":924560,"text":"\"Feminism for Men.\""},{"time":927280,"text":"And this was the first line\nof that article:"},{"time":930160,"text":"\"Feminism will make it possible\nfor the first time for men to be free.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":935160,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":936400,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}